<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1446,1699]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": WILSON" authorityYear="1964" box="[189,407,1446,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Aenictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villiersi">
<emphasis box="[189,407,1446,1475]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Aenictus villiersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1911" box="[704,818,1446,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Aenictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batesi">
<emphasis box="[704,818,1446,1475]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. batesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[884,1019,1446,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Aenictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decolor">
<emphasis box="[884,1019,1446,1475]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. decolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except for SIL considerably larger, the biggest of all the Afrotropical species (~100), subpetiolar process considerably smaller and shaped as a quarter of ellipse with its vertical side oriented forward, instead of subrectangular as in the other two sibling species. Petiole with dorsolateral ridges small but present, extending to the spiracle; in dorsal view forming a small flat platform differentiable from petiolar node (this character also present in some 
<emphasis box="[883,1015,1633,1662]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. decolor</emphasis>
samples). Also see discussion under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Donisthorpe" authorityYear="1942" box="[269,438,1670,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Aenictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidentatus">
<emphasis box="[269,438,1670,1699]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">A. bidentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
